      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Huntington_XXXX_1838_07_14_page01.jpg"/>
            <p>
               <note>2/197</note>
               Miss <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Edgeworth</persName>'s Compliments<lb/>
               to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ThomX1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.</persName> and M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ThomX2">Thomas</persName> and<lb/>
               she returns them sincere<lb/>
               thanks for the <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#JM">Jamaica</placeName> pepper<lb/>
               which they have been so good<lb/>
               to send her - She is obliged<lb/>
               particularly by their <unclear>attention</unclear>
               <lb/>
               in thinking of what she <choice>
                  <orig>particu<lb/>
                  -larly</orig>
                  <reg>particularly</reg>
               </choice> likes - and she begs her<lb/>
               thanks to M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ThomX2">Thomas</persName>'s brother<lb/>
               for having brought it over<lb/>
               for her<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworthtown</placeName>
                  <lb/>
                  <date when="1838-07-14"/>July 14<hi rend="superscript">h</hi>. 1838.<lb/>
               </dateline>
            </closer>
         </div>
